reviews.text: Great location for a break and plenty of  choices with food and drinks. Coffee was excellent. The chocolate lava cake was amazing👍

Delicious pork rack!
Excellent location and table is available at Friday night without booking!!

The waiters are very blunt, dark frown face, give single word answers. Only one third full house, still paid no attention to customers standing at the entrance waiting. I asked whether the item has any paster to come with. She said "NO." And before I could point to her the other item on the menu, she has already turned away. Typical Hong Kong young woman, 港女。

A good place to meet up with friends for tea. Their breakfast, dinner and lunch options are pretty good, better than the Central branch (near BoA). Have to wait to be seated, so I think they can increase their staff count. There are a variety of choices for sweet and savory food (unlike other branches) and their drinks options are quite good.

This place doesn't have any windows, but they play that theme well by decorating it like a dungeon, which is actually lovely. The wifi is great and the service too, but the Matcha Latte was $7.50 USD and that's a little bit pricey for a matcha latte.
